11. Security Considerations
Authentication: JWT with short-lived access tokens (15 min) and refresh tokens (7 days). Refresh tokens stored in HTTP-only cookies. Access tokens sent as Bearer headers.
File handling: PDF uploads validated for MIME type and size (max 5MB). Files stored outside the web root with UUID names, not original filenames. Virus scan with ClamAV on upload (optional, but recommended).
GitHub API: Calls made server-side only. No user GitHub token required for public repos. The user's GitHub username/URL never reaches the frontend raw; it is validated as a real GitHub resource before the job starts.
LLM prompt injection: Resume text and JD text are passed to the LLM inside delimited sections (<resume>, <jd_text>) with a system prompt instructing the model to treat content as data, not instructions. This does not fully prevent injection but significantly reduces risk.
Rate limiting: FastAPI middleware limits /analyze to 5 requests per user per hour. GitHub API rate limits are handled with exponential backoff and a shared token pool if needed.
CORS: Strict origin whitelist (only the Vercel frontend domain).
SQL injection: All database access via SQLAlchemy ORM with parameterized queries.

