13. Future Extension Points
The architecture is deliberately designed so that adding agents requires zero changes to the core infrastructure. To add a new agent (e.g. LinkedIn, Interview, Cover Letter):

Create agents/new_agent.py implementing BaseAgent.
Add a new node function in graph/nodes.py.
Add the node and edge to graph/graph.py.
Add a new column or row to agent_results table.
Add a new section to the frontend dashboard.

Nothing else changes. The shared state schema is the contract.
Other extension points: Redis for caching GitHub API responses (avoid re-fetching the same username within 1 hour), WebSocket for real-time status instead of polling, a vector database (Chroma or Pinecone) for storing past resumes and doing similarity matching across job descriptions.

14. Implementation Roadmap & Milestones
Week 1 — Foundation

Set up repo structure, FastAPI boilerplate, PostgreSQL schema, Alembic migrations, JWT auth, PDF upload endpoint. No LangGraph yet.
Week 2 — LangGraph Core

Implement CareerOSState, the graph skeleton with all four nodes as stubs returning mock data. Verify state flows end to end with a Celery task. The goal is the plumbing works before any agent logic.
Week 3 — Resume + JD Agents

Build PDFService with pdfplumber. Implement Resume agent prompt and post-processing. Implement JD agent. Write unit tests for both with fixture PDFs.
Week 4 — ATS Agent

Implement the 7-component scoring pipeline. This is the most logic-heavy piece — the deterministic parts (keyword intersection, action verb scan) should be tested separately from the LLM call.
Week 5 — GitHub Agent

Implement GitHubService with all required API calls. Handle rate limiting. Implement scoring logic. Test with public repos.
Week 6 — Frontend Core

Build the analysis submission flow (upload + form). Build the polling hook. Build the dashboard with skeleton loaders and progressive section reveal.
Week 7 — Integration + Polish

Wire everything together end to end. Handle edge cases (PDF parse failure, private GitHub account, rate limit hit). Add error states to the UI. Write integration tests.
Week 8 — Hardening

Security review: CORS, input validation, prompt injection mitigations. Performance: check LangGraph job latency, add GitHub response caching. Documentation: README, API docs via FastAPI's automatic OpenAPI.

